From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dynamic Devices <support@dynamicdevices.co.uk>
Date: Wed, 11 Jun 2026 14:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] ASoC: pcm6240: skip PRE_POWER_UP on capture unmute (DT510)

0005 removed PRE_POWER_UP from pcmdevice_startup, but .mute_stream still
calls pcmdevice_mute(unmute) on capture open via the ASoC core. That replays
regbin PRE_POWER_UP and resets Ch1 Digi (0x52=0xf0) before the first sample.

ASI bring-up remains in pcmdevice_asi_capture_enable (0004/0005 startup).
Keep PRE_SHUTDOWN on capture mute (stream close).

Signed-off-by: Dynamic Devices <support@dynamicdevices.co.uk>
---
 sound/soc/codecs/pcm6240.c | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/sound/soc/codecs/pcm6240.c b/sound/soc/codecs/pcm6240.c
--- a/sound/soc/codecs/pcm6240.c
+++ b/sound/soc/codecs/pcm6240.c
@@ -1953,6 +1953,10 @@ static int pcmdevice_mute(struct snd_soc_dai *dai, int mute, int stream)
 		return -EINVAL;
 	}
 
+	/* Capture unmute: PRE_POWER replays Ch1 Digi; ASI is in startup (0004/0005). */
+	if (!mute && stream == SNDRV_PCM_STREAM_CAPTURE)
+		return 0;
+
 	if (mute)
 		block_type = PCMDEVICE_BIN_BLK_PRE_SHUTDOWN;
 	else
